<html>
  <body>

    <!-- Address section -->
    <table width="100%">
      <tr>
        <td align="left"><%= sender.get_attr('name') %></td>
        <td align="right"><%= client.get_attr('name') %></td>
      </tr>

      <tr>
        <td align="left"><%= sender.get_attr('address') %></td>
        <td align="right"><%= client.get_attr('address') %></td>
      </tr>

      <tr>
        <td align="left"><%= sender.get_attr('postcode') %></td>
        <td align="right"><%= client.get_attr('postcode') %></td>
      </tr>
    </table>

    <h1><%= @template['name'] %></h1>

    <h3>Forward</h3>

    <p>This is an example document, designed to what sort of data legalapp
    currently represents.</p>

    <p>Eventually, the structure of the documents will be composable, using
    various template bits of content to produce large and complex
    documents.</p>

    <p>House styles will be able to be added to the document, by uploading
    template .docx files.</p>

    <h3>User-defined Paragraph content</h3>

    <i>This is content which is defined by the user - probably from a textbox
      in the UI - a good example of this might be Funeral details</i>

    <%= paragraph_content(:example_paragraph_content) %>

    <h3>User-defined Interpolated Paragraph content</h3>

    <i>This is content which is customisable by the user, but also is capable
      of adding in custom content from other datasources.</i>

    <%= paragraph_content(:interpolated_content) %>

    <h4>Some content here refers to data that doesn't exist:</h4>

    <%= paragraph_content(:interpolated_content_with_errors) %>

    <h3>Loopable content</h3>

    <i>This is content which can be iterated over - a good example of this is
    the "specific legacies" section of a will:</i>

    <%= render partial: 'document_templates/shared/beneficiary_specific_legacy' %>

  </body>
</html>
